            {
                "question_type": "Application/Performance",
                "question": "Does the ALE process show potential for CMOS applications?",
                "answer_type": "Paragraph",
                "answer": "The image f benchmarks the maximum gm as a function of Wf for InGaAs FinFETs as well as state-of-the-art Si FinFETs. Among the InGaAs FinFETs, the devices in this paper are the most aggressively scaled in the width dimension. In addition to the results listed above for Wf = 2.5 nm, the InGaAs FinFET in\nthis paper demonstrated a record gm at Wf below 20 nm. The gm of the InGaAs FinFETs around Wf = 7 nm also approaches that of the second generation Si FinFETs despite a lower VDD = 0.5 V and longer gate length. These results highlight the great potential of this novel technique for future generations of CMOS technology and other device applications."
